tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE quantum_algorithms (
    algorithm_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_name VARCHAR(255),
    description TEXT,
    parallelization_strategy VARCHAR(50)
)

CREATE TABLE Algorithm_Implementations (
	implementation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	algorithm_id INT,
	implementation_name VARCHAR(255),
	parallelization_support BOOL,
	FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES Quantum_Algorithms (algorithm_id)
);

CREATE TABLE QuantumComputers (
    computer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    brand VARCHAR(255),
    qubits_count INT,
    used_qubits INT,
    available_qubits INT
);

CREATE TABLE AlgorithmParallelization (
    parallel_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    algorithm_id INT,
    computer_id INT,
    parallelization_status VARCHAR(50),
    FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES QuantumAlgorithms(algorithm_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (computer_id) REFERENCES QuantumComputers(computer_id)
);
CREATE TABLE quantum_algorithms ( algorithm_id INT PRIMARY KEY, algorithm_name VARCHAR(255), parallelization_level INT );
CREATE TABLE quantum_tasks ( task_id INT PRIMARY KEY, task_name VARCHAR(255), algorithm_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (algorithm_id) REFERENCES quantum_algorithms(algorithm_id) );
CREATE TABLE quantum_workers ( worker_id INT PRIMARY KEY, worker_name VARCHAR(255), task_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (task_id) REFERENCES quantum_tasks(task_id) );
CREATE TABLE quantum_results ( result_id INT PRIMARY KEY, task_id INT, result_data TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (task_id) REFERENCES quantum_tasks(task_id) );
CREATE TABLE quantum_errors ( error_id INT PRIMARY KEY, task_id INT, error_message TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (task_id) REFERENCES quantum_tasks(task_id) );
